<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>They recently gave birth within 24 hours of each other.</p>

<p>And on Sunday, twins Nikki and Brie Bella posted new photos of their babies to Instagram.</p>

<p>Brie shared a snap of son Buddy in a brown onesie with white stitching made to look a like a football, while Nikki showed off son Mateo wearing a stripy onesie.</p>

<p>Family Sunday: Brie Bella shared a new photo to Instagram on Sunday, showing herself with husband Daniel Bryan, daughter Birdie, three, and newborn son Buddy, born September 1</p>

<p>'Sunday laughs': Brie's twin sister Nikki also updated fans with some new pics of her baby boy Mateo, born August 31</p>

<p>The former pro wrestlers, 36, who turned their sports careers into reality TV fame with The Bellas, are doting on their new arrivals.</p>

<p>Nikki gave birth to her first child on August 31. She shares Mateo with her fiance, the DWTS pro dancer Artem Chigvintsev.</p>

<p>Brie delivered Buddy on September 1, and he's a baby brother for daughter Birdie, three, whom she shares with husband and WWE star Daniel Bryan, 39. </p>

<p>Cousins: Buddy was dressed in a brown onesie with white stitching made to look a like a football, while Mateo wore a stripy onesie and his hair was brushed up at the front</p>

<p>Siblings: Buddy's older sister Birdie clearly dotes on her new brother</p>

<p>Brie has been married to Daniel since April 2014 and while she is retired, he continues to wrestle in the WWE SmackDown brand on Friday nights.</p>

<p>Brie announced her retirement from the WWE in March 2019 after 11 years and her twin sister Nikki also stepped away from the ring at the same time. </p>

<p>The sisters now star on the reality TV series Total Bellas and have their own podcast called The Bellas. </p>

<p>Set to wed: Nikki shares her first child with fiance and DWTS pro dancer Artem Chigvintsev</p>
